				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Two pets would be almost to power and yes a little bit more of a handful to control.  You'd have to have 2 pet windows, and remember to make both attack and both backoff at the right time.  It'd be useful if you wanted to solo in an area, where you don't have to worrya bout sending on wrong creature and other like predicaments.
<br />

<br />
Could go the Bonedancer route from DAoC a little.   Where you have your main pet and can summon another pet of a lower level who follows main pet and attacks what he attacks, Backs off when he backs off.  
<br />

<br />
But then like said before could be a temporary pet, AA ability where you click the AA hotkey, start to cast the 2nd pet.  This sets off a timer for the AA and ends after such a time and the 2nd pet is gone.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
